de.sub.goobi.metadaten.copier

Class CopyIfMetadataIsAbsentRule

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.sub.goobi.metadaten.copier.DataCopyrule
      • de.sub.goobi.metadaten.copier.CopyIfMetadataIsAbsentRule

  • public class CopyIfMetadataIsAbsentRule
extends DataCopyrule
    The CopyIfMetadataIsAbsentRule defines that a metadata is copied right to left in case that the structure node defined on the left exists but doesn’t yet have a metadata as named. Examples: /@CurrentNoSorting ""= /*[0]@CurrentNoSorting − copy the sort number form the first child to the top struct if it doesn’t have a sort number yet /*[0]@TitleDocMain ""= /@TitleDocMain − copy the main title from the top struct to its first child element if it doesn’t have a main tile yet
    Author:
    Matthias Ronge <matthias.ronge@zeutschel.de>
